# S2-5: Prisma Enum Migration

Refactor the database schema to use formal Prisma `enum` types for fields that represent a fixed set of values (e.g., statuses, modes, and roles).

## Proposed Changes

### [Database] [prisma/schema.prisma](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/prisma/schema.prisma) [MODIFY]
Create the following enums and update the corresponding models:

- **`enum AccessMode`**: `OPEN`, `PRIVATE`
- **`enum TurnMode`**: `FREESTYLE`, `STRUCTURED`
- **`enum LogStatus`**: `ACTIVE`, `COMPLETED`
- **`enum Category`**: `FREEWRITING`, `HAIKU`, `POEM`, `SHORT_NOVEL`
- **`enum UserRole`**: `USER`, `ADMIN`
- **`enum TargetType`**: `TURN`, `LOG`
- **`enum ReportStatus`**: `PENDING`, `DISMISSED`, `ACTIONED`
- **`enum ModAction`**: `HIDE_TURN`, `CLOSE_LOG`, `DISMISS`

**Note**: For `Category`, I will convert the existing mixed-case strings (e.g., "Freewriting") to upper-case enum variants (e.g., `FREEWRITING`) for consistency, and update the existing data in the migration.

